Bank Rakyat Indonesia, Medco, Timah: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-06-16T02:04:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-16/bank-rakyat-indonesia-medco-timah-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  rose 0.6 percent to 3,794.25.  Energy companies: Crude oil for July delivery slumped 4.6
percent to $94.81 a barrel in  New York  yesterday, settling below
$95 for the first time since February.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ),  Indonesia ’s
biggest listed oil company, rose 2.1 percent to 2,450 rupiah and
PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the second largest, declined 2
percent to 193 rupiah.  PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia (BBRI IJ): The company’s Islamic
banking arm,  PT Bank Syariah BRI , may sell sukuk, or Shariah-
compliant bonds, in the next one to two years to support
expansion, President Director Ventje Rahardjo said. Bank Rakyat,
Indonesia’s largest lender by revenue, rose 1.6 percent to 6,400
rupiah.  PT Timah (TINS IJ): Tin for three-month delivery in  London 
dropped 1.4 percent, extending yesterday’s 2 percent slump.
Timah, Indonesia’s largest tin producer, lost 1 percent to 2,500
rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  